Respond to requests for help in breakout sessions
During a breakout session, attendees can click "Ask for help" if they have a question or need assistance. As a host, you'll see a message when an attendee has requested help. You can join the breakout session to answer their question.
This feature is supported on Webex Meetings. On Webex App, this feature is available on our Video Mesh-ready meeting platform.
Desktop
Mobile
When the message appears, click Join session to join the breakout session immediately.
To join the session later, click Join later.
When you're ready to join the breakout session, click Join next to the name of the breakout session in the Breakout sessions tab of the Participants panel.
In the Breakout sessions tab, appears next to the name of the attendee who asked for help.
If the breakout session is collapsed, appears next to the name of the breakout session.